text: The Division of Fraser was an Australian Electoral Division in the Australian Capital Territory and the Jervis Bay Territory. It was set up in 1974 when the Division of Australian Capital Territory was changed. It is named for Jim Fraser, who was member for Australian Capital Territory 1951-70. It includes the area north of the Molonglo River and Lake Burley Griffin, Belconnen, Gungahlin, and North Canberra. It also includes Jervis Bay Territory. ==Members== Member Party Term Ken Fry Labor 1974–1984 John Langmore Labor 1984–1996 Steve Dargavel Labor 1997–1998 Bob McMullan Labor 1998–2010 Andrew Leigh Labor 2010–present ==Election results== * 2004 election results * 2007 election results * 2010 election results * 2013 election results ==References== ==Other websites== * Division of Fraser - Australian Electoral Commission * Andrew Leigh's website Category:Former electoral divisions of Australia Category:1974 establishments in Australia
